merous fields, including gender studies, performance studies, subaltern studies, and comparative cultural studies. Quite apart from their importance as theater, these plays are crucial for a fully rounded understanding of the cultural dynamics involved in the transition from Maoist to post-Mao China, from socialist realist drama to the post-socialist response to a market economy and a society in flux.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aChen, Xiaomei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Xiaomei, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDenton, Kirk A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGunn, Edward M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMa, Yuanxi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Philip F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWong, Timothy C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWu, Charles Qianzhi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066325940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082484511740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824845117423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780824845117/original  a978-3-11-056414-3  UHP eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-066325-9  University